Combine @olive oil{1/4%cup}, @soy sauce{2 1/2%tablespoons}, and @steak seasoning{1%teaspoon} into a marinade.

Put marinade and pork chops in a #1 gallon resealable plastic bag{}.

Set bag in #baking dish{} and refrigerate for ~{3%hours} to ~{8%hours}.

Sear for ~{2%minutes} to ~{3%minutes} per side at 450 degrees F.

Grill at 350-400 degrees F for ~{6%minutes} to ~{8%minutes} per side.

Check for internal temperature between 145-160 degrees F.

Tent in foil for ~{5%minutes} to ~{7%minutes}.
